{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> διατρῐβή</b>, ἡ, <br /> <b>wearing away,</b> especially of Time, <b>way</b> or <b>manner of spending,</b> χρόνου τε διατριβὰς.. ἐφηῦρε.. πεσσοὺς κύβους τε <b>pastimes,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 479.2: hence, _absolutely_, \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__1</b></Level3> <b>pastime, amusement,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 923, 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 219.4, etc.; ἐν συνουσίᾳ τινὶ καὶ δ. 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.71; γέλωτα καὶ δ. παρέχειν τινί 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.175, compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Timoleon” 11; τοῦ συμποσίου δ. 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 185; παρέσχε τοῖς κωμικοῖς δ. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>materiem jocandi,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pericles” 4, compare 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Orationes” 2.52b \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; <b>place of amusement,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 481.10, 3rd c.BC: Bato Comicus 2.4. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>serious occupation, study,</b> etc., τοὺς ἐν φιλοσοφίᾳ καὶ τῇ τοιᾷδε δ. τεθραμμένους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 172c; διατριβὰς ποιεῖσθαι περί τι 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 16.11, compare 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 11.37; πρός τι 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 2.38; ἐπί τινι 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 1498; ἡ δ. τὰ πολλὰ ἐν λόγοις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Lysis” 204a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.b</b></Level4> <b>discourse,</b> τὰς ἐμὰς δ. καὶ τοὺς λόγους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ap.” 37d, compare “Grg.” 484e, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.19, etc.; αἱ πολιτικαὶ δ. 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 10.15. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.c</b></Level4> <b>short ethical treatise</b> or <b>lecture,</b> δ. βραχέος διανοήματος ἠθικοῦ ἔκτασις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Hermogenes Rhetor “περὶ μεθόδου δεινότητος” 5, compare 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus: title of works by Zeno, Cleanthes, etc. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.d</b></Level4> <b>school</b> of philosophy, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 5.211d, +others, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Alex.” 5; Μωυσοῦ καὶ Χριστοῦ 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 8.579; Ἐπικούρου δ. 2nd c.AD: Numenius Apamensis Platonicus cited in 4th c.AD: Eusebius Caesariensis Scriptor Ecclesiasticus “Praeparatio Evangelica” 14.5 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; also, <b>a place of teaching, school,</b> ἡ ἐν τῷ κήπῳ δ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 217, compare 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “Academicorum Index” p.39 M., 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Nigr.” 25, 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 8.350b. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>way of life, passing of time,</b> δ. ἐν ἀγορᾷ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1055; δ. νέων ἐν δικαστηρίοις 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.32 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ ἐν Σικελίᾳ δ. <b>stay</b> there, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Epistulae” 337e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ποιεῖσθαι ἐν τῷ ὑγρῷ τὴν δ., ἐν τῇ γῇ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 487a20, “Resp.” 474b26; διατριβὰς μετ᾽ ἀλλήλων διατρίβειν 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.147. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>place of resort, haunt,</b> τὰς ἐν Λυκείῳ δ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthyphro” 2a; ᾖα ἐπὶ τὰς συνήθεις δ. [prev. author] “Chrm.” 153a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> in bad